BASIC GIT COMMANDS SUMMARY :

git init: Initialize a new repository.
git add: Stage files for commit.
git commit: Commit staged files.
git status: Show the status of the working directory.
git pull: Fetch and merge changes from a remote repository.
git push: Push changes to a remote repository.
git branch: Manage branches.
git branch "name of the branch": create new branches.
git checkout: Switch between branches.
git log : View commit history.
git diff : to check the changes in the file.
git checkout "name of the new branch" : to change between branches.

FOR ADDING NEW REPOSITORY :

git init => (add git into directory).
git add (check files > ls, ls -a.).
git commit -m "(name of the commit)"(to check status > git status, git log).
git remote add origin "git link".
git push -u origin main.

TO REMOVE FROM STAGING AREA LOCAL REPOSITARY :

git rm --cached -r .
git rm --cached -r <file-name>

TO ADD NEW PROJECT FROM GITHUB TO LOCAL REPPOSITORY :

git clone "url".
cd "directory"
npm install.
npm start.

FOR MERGING AND CLONING NEW PROJECTS FROM GITHUB :

git branch "name of the branch"
git merge "name of the branch"